      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double VANOS. This driver-focused example utilizes a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox delivering power to the rear wheels via a factory limited-slip differential. To ensure mechanical longevity, the rod bearings have been addressed and the rear subframe has been reinforced to mitigate common chassis fatigue. The suspension geometry remains tight with upgraded bushings and Bilstein dampers, providing the tactile feedback these longitudinal-engine platforms are known for. While displaying minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-loved enthusiast vehicle, the powertrain remains robust with a linear power band and an 8,000 RPM redline. A mechanically sound specimen for the discerning purist.",
